cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.MA 

The paper presents a reinforcement learning algorithm that learns to display reciprocal behavior towards co-players in complex sequential social dilemmas. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category, as it involves developing a learning algorithm. Additionally, the paper deals with game theory and social interaction, which suggests that it could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also discusses pro-social outcomes and the influence of co-players' behavior, which suggests that it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) category.
